OL,6,FBoth Hong Kong and officials in
OL,7,FBeijing have argued that the national
OL,8,Fsecurity law does not suppress
OL,9,Ffreedoms, saying it has instead ended
OL,10,Fchaos and "restored stability" to the
OL,11,Fcity.
OL,13,FWhat is Hong Kong's national security
OL,14,Flaw?
OL,16,FOfficially called the "Law of the
OL,17,FPeople's Republic of China on
OL,18,FSafeguarding National Security in the
OL,19,FHong Kong Special Administrative
OL,20,FRegion", it was passed in 2020.
