OL,6,FSupporters of the convicted say they
OL,7,Fwere simply taking part in opposition
OL,8,Fpolitics that was once allowed in Hong
OL,9,FKong, and that the court verdict marks
OL,10,FChina's control over the once-
OL,11,Foutspoken city.
OL,13,FIn Hong Kong, the city's governing
OL,14,Fassembly is now comprised with pro-
OL,15,FBeijing loyalists, with most pro-
OL,16,Fdemocracy figures either in jail or in
OL,17,Fexile.
